**Repo opened per-call with no connection pooling or caching**: Every tool call opens a new `Repository` via `open_repo()`. `git2::Repository::open` is not free -- it parses config, reads HEAD, and sets up internal state. Under concurrent MCP tool calls (which the protocol allows), this means multiple independent `Repository` handles to the same `.git` directory, with no coordination. While libgit2 handles concurrent readers reasonably well, concurrent writers (e.g., two `create_issue` calls) will race on ref updates and one will fail with a lock error. Consider holding a single `Repository` (behind a `Mutex` if needed) or at least documenting the concurrency model.